events.name: TensorFlow for Beginners

venue.name: L201, 2nd Floor, Immaculate Conception Bldg, University of the Immaculate Conception

events.description:
TensorFlow is an open-source software library for Machine Intelligence. It is being used to power a number of Google services involving various perceptual and natural language understanding tasks. The library of algorithms allows computer systems to mimic human's ability to learn and reason. TensorFlow was originally developed by researchers working on the Google Brain Team with Google's Machine Intelligence research organization.

This lecture provides a quick overview of the background and functionalities of TensorFlow, as well as its wide array of application areas. Basic concepts needed to give you a head start in using the library will also be covered.

events.name: Building Apps for the Google Assistant
events.description:

The Google Assistant's mission is to help users get things done in their world. This session will explain how to plug into the Google Assistant services ecosystem. We'll cover from understanding the business use case and high-level user interface design to implementation and growing usage. events.name: Introduction to webcomponents via Polymer

venue.name: mClinica
venue.address_1: C2 Building, Bonifacio High Street Central, 7th Avenue

events.description:
• What we'll do
2018 will be the year of frameworks adopting webcomponents, as all major browsers support the standard natively without the need for polyfills.

In our first session on webcomponents we will give an introduction what they are and how you can build your first simple webcomponent via the Polymer library. We see this event as an introduction session to get to know each other and see where to take the topic in the future, whether you want a focus on Polymer, blazingly fast and small vanillajs webcomponents or topics such as integrating with frameworks like React.

events.name: Introduction to Kotlin

venue.name: Acceler8 - Paseo de Roxas (New)
venue.address_1: LG1, 111 Paseo de Roxas, Legaspi Village

events.description:
• What we'll do
Java has been the language for Android ever since it started. Not anymore. Kotlin is now an official language on Android.

Kotlin is a statically typed programming language that runs on the JVM and is completely interoperable with Java. Kotlin is an officially supported language for developing Android apps, along with Java.

In this event, we will learn the basics of Kotlin, create an Android app using it, and during the session we'll see why you should make the switch from Java to Kotlin

*Professionals are prioritized for this event

• What to bring
- Laptop with Android Studio 3.0 and the SDK Tools installed
Android Phone with USB cable https://developer.android.com/studio/index.html#downloads

• Important Reminders
- Before applying assess your availability and commitment first. We want to prioritize and give slots to those who really want to learn.

events.description:
• What we'll do
TensorFlow Lite is TensorFlow's lightweight solution for mobile and embedded devices. It enables on-device machine learning inference with low latency and a small binary size. TensorFlow Lite also supports hardware acceleration with the Android Neural Networks API.

In this event, we will learn the basics of TensorFlow Lite, and create an Android app using it.
